      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A hearing in case in which it\nwas Indian against Greek was\nheld before United States Com\nmissioner Marshall this after\nnoon in the Hutton building. The\nGreek, Nick Kahes. is al saloon\nand hotel keeper at Tekoa and\nwas arrested for giving a quart\nof whiskey to Johnnie Moctlemay,\nan Indian of the Occur d'Alene\nreservation.\n\n\nThe Greek could not speak Eng\nfish and had to have an Interpreter,\nwhile the Indian could give a few\ngrunts that were construed as the\nAmerican tongue. Kahes was\nbound over to the federal court\nunder bond of 5000 and at last\nreport his friend were shaping up\nthe bond."
    }
  ]
